2. Myſtically, or Allegorically, and ſo we may underſtand by the feet of the Saints, their ſouls affections

for God, their ardent deſires towards him, their reſolutions to walk in the way of his commandments:
Auſt. For Deum adimus animo, non vehiculo: They are inward affections, raiſed and blown up by the Almighty's inſpiration, that carry the Spouſe as in the Chariots of Amminadab to the Shulamite and Bride-groom of her ſoul, Cant. 6.12. And here God hath indiſpenſably bound himſelf, that they that truly ſeek him, ſhall as truly find him, Mat. 7.7.
